-- Hulu Names Disney Executive Paul as CFO
-- B y   A n d y   F i x m e r
-- 2013-10-25T18:53:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-25/hulu-names-disney-executive-paul-as-cfo.html
Hulu LLC, the video-streaming site
owned by three media companies, named Elaine Paul, a  Walt Disney
Co. (DIS)  executive, as its chief financial officer.  Paul replaces Tom Fuelling, Hulu Chief Executive Officer
Mike Hopkins said today in a blog post. Paul was involved in
Disney’s original investment in Hulu in 2009 and was senior vice
president of corporate strategy at Disney.  Hulu, which offers a free, ad-supported service and the
$7.99-a-month Hulu Plus, with more shows available on more
devices, is owned by Disney, 21st Century Fox Inc. and  Comcast
Corp. (CMCSA) ’s NBCUniversal. Hopkins, a former Fox executive, was named
CEO of Hulu last week.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andy Fixmer in  Los Angeles  at 
 afixmer@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Anthony Palazzo at 
